# React + Vite + Tailwind CSS Setup Guide

This guide explains everything step-by-step:

* How to create a React app using Vite
* How to install Tailwind CSS
* How to run the project
* Folder structure basics
* How to add components
* How to use Tailwind classes
* Important commands
* Build and deployment basics

---

# 1. Install Node.js

First install Node.js from the official website:

[https://nodejs.org/](https://nodejs.org/)

After installation check version:

```bash
node -v
npm -v
```

If versions are showing correctly then setup is complete.

---

# 2. Create React App Using Vite

Open terminal and run:

```bash
npm create vite@latest
```

Then:

```bash
Project name: my-app
Framework: React
Variant: JavaScript
```

Move into project folder:

```bash
cd my-app
```

Install dependencies:

```bash
npm install
```

Run project:

```bash
npm run dev
```

Vite will give a local URL like:

```bash
http://localhost:5173/
```

Open it in browser.

---

# 3. Project Folder Structure

Basic structure:

```bash
my-app/
│
├── public/
├── src/
│   ├── assets/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── App.jsx
│   ├── main.jsx
│
├── package.json
├── vite.config.js
└── node_modules/
```

### Important Files

| File           | Purpose              |
| -------------- | -------------------- |
| App.jsx        | Main component       |
| main.jsx       | React entry point    |
| package.json   | Project dependencies |
| vite.config.js | Vite configuration   |

---

# 4. Install Tailwind CSS

Install Tailwind:

```bash
npm install tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite
```

Update `vite.config.js`

```js
import { defineConfig } from 'vite'
import react from '@vitejs/plugin-react'
import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite'

export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react(), tailwindcss()],
})
```

---

# 5. Configure Tailwind CSS

Open:

```bash
src/index.css
```

Add:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
```

Now Tailwind is ready.

---

# 6. Use Tailwind CSS Classes

Example:

```jsx
function App() {
  return (
    <div className="h-screen bg-black text-white flex items-center justify-center">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold text-green-400">
        Hello Tailwind CSS
      </h1>
    </div>
  )
}

export default App
```

---

# 7. Create Components

Create folder:

```bash
src/components
```

Create component:

```bash
Navbar.jsx
```

Example:

```jsx
function Navbar() {
  return (
    <nav className="bg-black text-white p-4">
      Navbar
    </nav>
  )
}

export default Navbar
```

Use inside App.jsx:

```jsx
import Navbar from './components/Navbar'

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Navbar />
    </div>
  )
}

export default App
```

---

# 8. Install React Icons

Install:

```bash
npm install react-icons
```

Use:

```jsx
import { FaGithub } from 'react-icons/fa'

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <FaGithub size={40} />
    </div>
  )
}
```

---

# 9. Install React Router

Install:

```bash
npm install react-router-dom
```

Basic setup:

```jsx
import { BrowserRouter, Routes, Route } from 'react-router-dom'

function App() {
  return (
    <BrowserRouter>
      <Routes>
        <Route path='/' element={<h1>Home</h1>} />
      </Routes>
    </BrowserRouter>
  )
}

export default App
```

---

# 10. Install Axios

Install:

```bash
npm install axios
```

Use:

```jsx
import axios from 'axios'
```

---

# 11. GitHub Push Commands

Initialize git:

```bash
git init
```

Add files:

```bash
git add .
```

Commit:

```bash
git commit -m "first commit"
```

Add branch:

```bash
git branch -M main
```

Connect GitHub repo:

```bash
git remote add origin YOUR_REPO_LINK
```

Push:

```bash
git push -u origin main
```

Force push if needed:

```bash
git push -u origin main --force
```

---

# 12. Build Project

Create production build:

```bash
npm run build
```

Preview build:

```bash
npm run preview
```

---

# 13. Common npm Commands

| Command         | Purpose                  |
| --------------- | ------------------------ |
| npm install     | Install dependencies     |
| npm run dev     | Start development server |
| npm run build   | Create production build  |
| npm run preview | Preview production build |

---

# 14. Common Errors

## node_modules issue

Fix:

```bash
rm -rf node_modules
npm install
```

Windows:

```bash
rmdir /s /q node_modules
npm install
```

---

## Port already in use

Close previous terminal or stop old server.

---

## Tailwind not working

Check:

* `@import "tailwindcss";` exists
* Tailwind installed correctly
* Restart Vite server

---

# 15. Best Practices

* Create reusable components
* Keep clean folder structure
* Use meaningful file names
* Push code regularly to GitHub
* Avoid uploading node_modules

---

# 16. Useful Extensions for VS Code

Recommended extensions:

* ES7+ React Snippets
* Tailwind CSS IntelliSense
* Prettier
* Auto Rename Tag
* Error Lens

